#Text=New sub-population of critically endangered species of monkey found
#Text=Biologists from Fauna and Flora International say that they had discovered up to twenty critically endangered monkeys in a remote forest in northwestern Vietnam .
#Text=The group , which belongs to the species of Tonkin snub-nosed monkeys , included three infant monkeys , an indication that they were breeding and increasing in their numbers .
#Text=Before the discovery , less than 250 of the animals were thought to inhabit the planet .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Michael McCarthy .
#Text=" A glimpse of hope for rare monkey " — The Independent , December 5 , 2008

column1: #Text=India announces $ 4 billion stimulus package
#Text=India has announced that it will release a stimulus package worth $ 4 billion , or 200 billion rupees , to help its economy , as the global economic slowdown continues .
#Text=This comes as the Reserve Bank of India cut its key interest rate by 1 % , from 7.5 % to 6.5 % , on Saturday to , encourage more spending .
#Text=The rates are at their lowest since June of 2006 .
#Text=This is the third time since October that the bank has cut its rates .
#Text=Business confidence in India has also been lowered after an attack on Mumbai last week left at least 170 people dead .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" India unveils $4bn stimulus plan " — BBC News Online , December 7 , 2008

column1: #Text=High turnout in Ghanian elections
#Text=Officials say that a high turnout has been recorded for elections for president and parliament in Ghana .
#Text=Despite long queues at polling stations , the election has been reported as peaceful .
#Text=12.4 million voters , approximately half the country 's population , have cast their ballots .
#Text=" Voter turnout is going to be very high , " said Electoral Commission Chairman Kwadwo Afari-Gyan .
#Text=" I should expect a higher number than we saw in the last elections because I could see this one is very competitive . "
#Text=Turnout in 2004 was a record 85 % .
#Text=The election results are expected to come in on Monday .
#Text=Sources
#Text="

#Text=' Turnout high ' in Ghana elections  — BBC News Online , December 7 , 2008

column1: #Text=Sudan deploys more troops to oil-rich state
#Text=The army of Sudan has deployed additional troops to the state of Kordofan , which is rich in oil .
#Text=The army told state media that it wanted to prevent " feverish attempts " to attack the area by Darfur rebels , members of the Justice and Equality Movement ( JEM ) .

#Text=The army 's announcement comes just days after officials in semi-autonomous southern Sudan accused the north of creating a large force in southern Kordofan over the period of the last three weeks .
#Text=The Sudanese army has been on alert since JEM launched an unprecedented attack on the Sudanese capital of Khartoum in May of this year .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Sudan build-up in oil-rich state " — BBC News Online , December 7 , 2008
#Text=" Sudan builds up troops in oil region " — Welt Online , December 7 , 2008
#Text=Walmart.com to stock up on Wiis starting Monday
#Text=On December 7 , 2008 , Walmart.com announced that it will have thousands of Wiis in stock online starting Monday .
#Text=The console will be sold for $ 249.24 alone , or for $ 329 in a " value bundle , " which includes the Wii console and other Wii items such as an extra pair of controllers .
#Text=The Wii has been one the most popular electronic items this season .
#Text=On Black Friday , retailers ran out of stock , forcing consumers to go online to sites such as Yahoo ! Shopping , eBay , and other big retailer sites .
#Text=By nightfall on Friday , the Wii console sold out on all big retailer sites including Walmart.com , BestBuy.com , and CircuitCity.com.
#Text=Sources :
#Text=Nicole Maestri .
#Text=" Walmart.com offers " thousands " of Wiis from Monday " — Reuters.com , Dec 7 , 2008
#Text=Luigi Lugmayr .
#Text=" Huge Wii Sale on Walmart to happen on Monday " — I4U News , Dec 7 , 2008
#Text=John Lester .
#Text=" Walmart Stocks Nintendo Wii For Online Sale " — NewsOXY , Dec 7 , 2008
